# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# FlopsyBot environment variables
# Copy to `.env` and fill in your values. Never commit `.env`.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━


# ── Workspace ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where state, memory, credentials, and logs live.
# Set to `.flopsy` (relative) to keep the workspace inside the repo,
# or an absolute path, or omit to fall back to ~/.flopsy.
FLOPSY_HOME=.flopsy


# ── Gateway ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Bearer token required by the management HTTP endpoint
# (`flopsy mgmt ping|status`). Binds to 127.0.0.1 only.
GATEWAY_TOKEN=


# ── LLM providers ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Fill in the providers you actually use; leave the rest blank.
# Agents reference models like `ollama:glm-4.6:cloud` or
# `anthropic:claude-sonnet-4` — provider is inferred from the prefix.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
NVIDIA_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=


# ── Search & research ─────────────────────────────────────
# Used by the `web` / `research` toolsets (flopsygraph prebuilt tools).
TAVILY_API_KEY=


# ── Channels ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# One section per messaging channel. Only fill in what you enable
# in `flopsy.json5` → `channels.<name>.enabled: true`.

# Telegram (BotFather token)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=

# Discord (bot token from the developer portal)
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# Line (channel access token + signing secret)
LINE_CHANNEL_ACCESS_TOKEN=
LINE_CHANNEL_SECRET=

# Slack (bot + signing secret + app-level token)
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=

# Google Chat (verification token from the Workspace app)
GOOGLE_CHAT_VERIFICATION_TOKEN=

# WhatsApp / Signal / iMessage — populate if/when enabled
# WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# SIGNAL_ACCOUNT=
# IMESSAGE_BLUEBUBBLES_URL=


# ── Inbound webhooks ──────────────────────────────────────
# Shared secret for HMAC verification of the webhook receiver.
WEBHOOK_SECRET=


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# MCP servers
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Path to src/mcp-servers/ — referenced as ${MCP_ROOT} in flopsy.json5.
MCP_ROOT=./src/mcp-servers

# Note: OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH lives inline in flopsy.json5 → mcp.servers.obsidian.env
# — paths aren't secrets so they don't need env-var indirection.

# ── Smart home ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Home Assistant (long-lived access token from your HA user profile).
HOME_ASSISTANT_URL=
HOME_ASSISTANT_TOKEN=

# ── Security / OSINT (for the aragorn agent) ──────────────
VIRUSTOTAL_API_KEY=
SHODAN_API_KEY=


# ── Integrations (API-token MCP servers) ──────────────────
NOTION_API_KEY=
TODOIST_API_KEY=
# TRELLO_API_KEY=
# TRELLO_TOKEN=


# ── Google OAuth (for gmail / calendar / drive MCP servers) ───────
# Needed by the in-process token refresh flow. Create a Desktop OAuth
# client at console.cloud.google.com → Credentials, then paste here.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=


# ── Spotify (for the spotify MCP server) ──────────────────────────
# Create an app at developer.spotify.com/dashboard and register the
# redirect URI from `flopsy.json5` (mcp.servers.spotify.redirectBase,
# default `http://127.0.0.1:8888/spotify`). Then paste the Client ID
# below and run `flopsy auth spotify` once. No client secret needed —
# we use PKCE.
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
